  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to investigate whether the supplementation of a medically supervised
      weight management program with a novel fibre supplement, improves body weight, body
      composition, and laboratory measurements in overweight and obese individuals. All subjects
      will participate in the medical weight management program however the intervention group will
      have 5 grams of a novel fibre supplemented to each meal while the control group will not.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
